/font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=503.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> quadding pointers</span><hr size=1> First off if you are trying with an unknown mob pull just one but use your AE spells.  If you can kill the one and have enough mana for 2 more spells you can kill 4.  Make sure you have extra mana because the ones that resist will not stop walking if there is another with it.<br> <br>Now alot of wizards pull with the flex staff, depending on the mob I either pull with snare (otters) or just run close and pull with agro (raptors)  After you have your 4 run around in a circle for 2 or 3 trips and snare.  Then just AE till they die.  <br><br>I always have magi and Manaskin up incase something goes wrong.  Might be good to have MR up a bit to stop the self snare too.<br><br>Hope that helps,<br>Plano Planesdrifter<br>60 Wizard of Fennin Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uorsmoxlorr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orsmo Xlorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/12/02 5:32:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=503.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://orsmo.freewebspace.com/images/sigpic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I want to learn to kite</span><hr size=1> Also go practice a couple times on mobs that couldn't possiblely kill you will you learn. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=66366">Orsmo Xlorr 57 Lvl Wizard</A><BR><table width="350" border="0" bgcolor="#996433"><tr bgcolor="#F0A268"><td width="125" bgcolor="#FFCCFF"><div align="center"><img src="http://orsmo.freewebspace.com/images/wizz.jpg" width=250 height=200> </table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unamtik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Namtik</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://lokicons.homestead.com/files/icon21.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/13/02 7:10:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=503.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> Only way too learn is to die over and over and over and over till finally it clicks. Best place would be TD at your lvl. Easy too quad just hard too find a rez. If you read the tutorial on TD you shouldnt die but a couple times.<br><br>Namtik <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utorcosiris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Torc Osiris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/13/02 12:23:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=503.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> I'd suggest doing a trial run on the mob you want to quad kite, use the AE you plan to use, but instead of pulling 4, just pull 1, snare it and use your ae spell to kill it.<br><br>In essence you just quadded 4 mobs, you'll use the same amount of mana on one as with four. Just less risk involved in manging one.<br><br>Next try 2 or 3, you'll need to learn how to *round em up* before snaring, plus if you have a resist and need to snare the ones that resisted. - then round em up again, and snare till none resist and they are all are on the same snare timer.<br><br>learn to use your external camera, It really helps a lot.<br><br>At first I used a little timer as soon as I snared so I knew when it would break. after a while you learn to judge how much time you have.<br><br>If you don't have the staff of temperate flux, go get one. that is everything people say it is, mana free agro rocks.<br><br>If you're doing the raptors, make sure you fresh levitate and jboot right before you start. that is the key thing.<br><br>SoE makes pulling a breeze, if you can get it, i highly recommend it. <br><br>Learn the terrain of where you plan on quadding, you need to know where mobs roam, if there are any traps (ala the grey) that you need to avoid. <br><br>Plan an escape route if things get too heavy. - long straight run line then an abscond.<br><br>good luck ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umalkum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malkum</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/13/02 8:24:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=503.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://syndication.8m.net/sigs/familiar.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..</span><hr size=1> /sigh you guys are starting this poor guy off way too early...Raptors his first quad, hell no! jeesus lol...his first time quading should be in Cobalt Scar..../sigh, you all should know this. CS is the easier place to quad kite, like everyone says, start with 1 Wyvern, then 2, then 4....round em up then run far then snare, then nuke til dead...if you take too long nuking, snare again to put timer back up again...ummm staff of the temperate flux, get it now if you dont have it, silly wizard...after you perfect this Wyvern thing, THEN move to TD for raptors...thats all i gotta say, hope i dont confuse you! =) <p><img src="http://syndication.8m.net/sigs/Malk2.jpg" alt=""><br><br>Malkum [Ex]<br>58 Evoker<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=141394>See whats under my dress, I mean robe!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unamtik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Namtik</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://lokicons.homestead.com/files/icon21.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/02 6:24:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=503.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> Yeah Malkum has a point. Try quadding greenies before dying too raptors and watching your exp go in the wrong direction. Only thing you wont pick up in CS would be handling resists and adds but youll get the basic point of how its done.<br><br>Namtik <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umerkusstormcrow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merkus Stormcrow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/02 10:47:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=503.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> If you go to CS watch out for the named wyvern, Yvolcarn, as he's unsnareable and unrootable. If you kill him you lose CoV faction I think. I've pulled him several times accidentally and had to gate out.<br><br>Edit: My typing sucks! <p>[font=Arial][b]<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=123067">Merkus Stormcrow</a>[/b][br][maroon]Mystic Circle of Power[br]Wizard[/font=Arial][br][/maroon]</font></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umerkusstormcrow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merkus Stormcrow</A> at: 8/15/02 3:04:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umalkum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malkum</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/18/02 6:05:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=503.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://syndication.8m.net/sigs/familiar.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I want to learn to kite</span><hr size=1> Yvolcarn isnt that bad, just make sure when entering the zone to quad, have gate/abscond up, nothing the matter there really.....easy stuff if you get adds, just run over the ocean (i usually have dmf/levi/soe) and it'll take them a long time to get to you, so abscond/gate out, easy as that...then gate back in or med up when you zone back from abscond =) easy stuff, nothing to fear really...and i advise not to attack Yvolcarn, i think he summons? correct? hehe, not good for casters! <p><img src="http://syndication.8m.net/sigs/Malk2.jpg" alt=""><br><br>Malkum [Ex]<br>58 Evoker<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=141394>See whats under my dress, I mean robe!</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umalkum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malkum</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 8/18/02 6:05:55 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table bor